# StoneCore — Setup Guide

## Folder Structure
```
stonecore/
├── config.php              ← DB connection
├── database.sql            ← Import in phpMyAdmin
├── products-loader.js      ← Add to index.html
├── api/
│   ├── products.php        ← GET all products
│   ├── add_product.php     ← POST add product
│   ├── edit_product.php    ← POST edit product
│   └── delete_product.php  ← GET delete product
├── admin/
│   └── index.html          ← Admin panel
└── img/                    ← Product images folder
```

## Step 1 — Database Setup
1. phpMyAdmin open karo
2. `database.sql` file import karo
3. Database `stonecore_db` ban jayega with sample data

## Step 2 — Config Update
`config.php` mein apna DB credentials daalo:
```php
define('DB_USER', 'your_username');
define('DB_PASS', 'your_password');
```

## Step 3 — Frontend Connect
`index.html` ke end mein yeh add karo (</body> se pehle):
```html
<script src="products-loader.js"></script>
```

## Step 4 — Admin Panel
Browser mein open karo:
```
http://localhost/stonecore/admin/
```

## API Endpoints
| Method | URL                          | Use              |
|--------|------------------------------|------------------|
| GET    | api/products.php             | All products     |
| POST   | api/add_product.php          | Add product      |
| POST   | api/edit_product.php         | Edit product     |
| GET    | api/delete_product.php?id=1  | Delete product   |